snippet.textDisplay: Hi Jeff, thank you so much for another video! I started watching your channel only 2 weeks ago and it has been really helpful and inspiring. I have tried a lot of workouts of yours already and I have felt that there is a difference on the first try. However, there are many exercises that I just cannot do because I would need gym equipment to do and that is why I am writing this to you for some advice. I cannot go to a gym because of my work, I work night shifts, irregular number of nights per week, and it will be like this for maybe 3 more years. So smart thing for me to do is to work out at home. I am 6 ft tall and 170 lb weight, I ride my bicycle daily and physically active. I can do a proper push up, nose touching the ground and all the way up, just the way you showed in another clip, about 12 - 15 to fail - my form start going wrong at around 13th rep. At home I have a pair of 7.5 kg (16.5 lb) and 10 kg (22 lb) dumbbells and an inclining crunch bench. I happen to be able to follow your one meal per day diet. In fact, I have been on intermittent fasting diet for a year and it feels natural to me to eat one big meal or two light meals per day, with snacks sometimes but I have never experienced a ‘sugar rush’ in my life. Last week, I have looked at the mirror and I really want thicker arms and chest. I am way too skinny on my upper body. I would like to know if it is possible to gain what I want with what I got: two sets of dumbbells, inclining bench, a bicycle and my own body. I guess I kinda want to hear an assurance to keep going or suggestion on trying something different. Thank you for your time and all the resources you put out there.
